    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine with VarioCam Plus. This example features the desirable G96 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. To ensure long-term reliability, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a ceramic dual-row solution, and the cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat and high-flow water pump. The chassis maintains excellent torsional rigidity, supported by a multi-link rear suspension and ventilated four-piston monobloc calipers. While the exterior shows minor stone chipping and light patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response remain sharp and linear.",
